IRS990.MissionDesc: Albany Pro Musica's mission is to perform a broad spectrum of quality choral music at the highest levels of artistic excellence that inspires and transforms our audiences and to provide exceptional educational experiences that advance the choral art amoung new generations of singers.
IRS990.Desc: Albany Pro Musica (APM) offers four series concerts each season plus numerous special performances with distinguished local, national, and international partners, with a deliberately curated repertoire that includes classical masterpieces from the choral canon, compositions from modern and contemporary composers, and popular selections form the worlds of Broadway, traditional, folk music and more. APM's composer-in-residence project has resulted in the commissioning and premiers of numerous new compositions. APM also provides several educational programs annually, including a High School Choral Festival, a competitive youth apprenticeship program, materclasses for students, and the Pro Musica International Choral Festival.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Endowment Funds are used towards the specific purpose of the donor including general operations of the Organization.
Form 990 is reviewed by the Board of Directors, including the Executive Director, prior to filing.
Compensation is reviewed annually by the Board of Directors for the Executive Director.
Compensation is reviewed annually by the Board of Directors for Key Employees.
Meeting minutes are taken and approved for all Board of Directors meetings.
Information is available upon written request, by either mail or e-mail.
The board is annually reminded of the requirement under the conflict of interest policy of the organization.
